== F.5 — When a Student Does Not Advance

If a student has not met Minimum Completion for two consecutive months in the same area, the Headmaster schedules a diagnostic session before the student proceeds. The student is not removed from the academy — they revisit the work that produced the gap, with targeted support.

After a written remediation note has been issued, the student has the period of the next month to address the gap. If the gap persists after a second month and a second remediation note, the Headmaster schedules a second diagnostic session.

After three diagnostic interventions in the same operative area without meaningful progress, the Headmaster may advise the student to pause formal enrolment and continue as an independent researcher with occasional mentorship. This is not removal — it is an acknowledgement that the academy's structured path may not fit the student's current mode of learning or life circumstances. The student remains welcome to reapply.

#doctrine[
  _There is no failure limit. What cannot be accepted is advancing to more complex material while foundational gaps remain unaddressed. The Stone does not form on a compromised foundation._
  #align(right)[— TTAO curriculum]
]

